data.reddit:
21F, 5’10”, 200lbs (weight fluctuates), white, symptoms for 2+ years, Utah USA, currently on venlafaxine for inherited anxiety.

I’ve gone from being pretty active to feeling sick with any physical activity quickly. Last summer I started taking mediations for depression/anxiety, and during the blood panels the dr noticed my iron levels were really high and my b12 was dangerously deficient. I got put on b12 injections, which didn’t improve anything after the 8 weeks, but then when we tested a month later they were back to normal but my vitamin D was deficient. 

I also have muscle and joint pain almost constantly. My back especially as well as my fingers and wrists. It always feels kind of like bloating, but I’m drinking enough water. 

I’m constantly fatigued, and I sweat a lot (possibly the venlafaxine). I tried to do 30 minutes of consistent cardio, which used to be no big deal, but spent the next four hours feeling like I was going to throw up.

I get nausea and diarrhea regularly, haven’t pinpointed any specific food relation, but if I go too long without eating it gets worse.

I was anorexic when I was 14. Same height I am now, 5’10”, got down to 98 lbs. parents didn’t believe in mental health so I was never treated and took a long time to get back to healthier weights, but the amenorrhea was only for about 6 months. 

Finally tested my liver—MRI, CT scan, ultrasound—found “severe infiltration of nonalcoholic fatty liver disease,” and a tumor that’s most likely benign but we need to look again in a few months to make sure it didn’t grow. 

I’m wondering why I got fatty liver disease even though my diet is not worse than most people’s and I am still at a healthy weight. Is the liver damage anorexia-related? What do I do to get better? Is weight loss the only solution?
